item.title: This is not a cake.
item.dc:creator: basketweaver
item.description:
Scrab_on_mars:

Where’s the 1920x1080 one?

Either you need to learn to crop a picture, or…

… you are already dealing with accepting the original PNG format of the wallpaper, so hogging resources with a 3+MB image isn’t an issue for you, and you will just set the wallpaper to “centered” and the image will auto-adjust to your system.

Cropping, of course, will allow you to get the image down to the right size, and also save it to a more optimized format, which might kill some of the quality, but leave more power for your computer to game with

item.title: This is not a cake.
item.dc:creator: Trilby
item.description:
Archive of my old wallpapers here.

Distoban Mockup. August 10th.

Download:
1280 x 720 ( 1.2 MB )

This is a mockup of Distoban, a video game I am developing with a good friend of mine, a MIT programmer who goes by the username of Juhkystar. It is a 2D arena SHMUP with an open world and a strong focus on storytelling and exploration. This mockup illustrates a slightly outdated concept. Our interpretation of the game world has changed since then to a less open aesthetic.

Sorry about the odd wallpaper size. We are going for a standard 720p resolution.

Grimdark Packman. March 24th.

Download:
1440 x 900 ( 0.9 MB )

Nazi Coin. March 21st.

Download:
3456 x 2304 ( 9.7 MB )
1440 x 900 ( 2.1 MB )

Before anyone gets any wrong ideas, I am not in any way supporting Nazism or fascism. However, I do like the aesthetic of this decrepit coin. Daresay, this wallpaper captures that aesthetic perfectly. Coin is nowhere as dramatic or impressive as it is in this pic.

My mother found this Nazi coin in eastern Ukraine. She unearthed it while working at our dacha many years ago. It is a 1940 issue of the 10 Reichspfennig denomination, I believe. We also found spent bullet casings from German and Soviet pistols in that field. Which gets the imagination going, does it not, hmm?
